          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Target holder consists of a diamond plate coated with a",
                "metallic layer (area = 20X20 mm2, thickness t=1 mm)",
                "and heated by current flow.  A given metal sheet (a =",
                "15X17 mm2) is placed on top of the diamond plate with",
                "interim plates (from bottom to top) of MACOR (t = 1",
                "mm), Cu (t = 3 mm) and MACOR (t=1 mm).  At the centre",
                "of the top MACOR plate there is a hole of = 5 mm",
                "diameter, filled with another diamond of cylindrical",
                "shape and 2 mm height: it provides the thermal contact",
                "to the metal foil. The metal foil is electrically",
                "insulated for current measurement. Thermal elements",
                "measure the temperature at the diamond plate and the",
                "metal foil (near the area of the ion beam spot). For",
                "example, for t=340 centigrade the diamond plate had to",
                "have a temperature of 750 centigrade, which was the",
                "maximum for the present set-up;  above these",
                "temperatures, the insulators started to lose their",
                "electrical insulations more and more.",
                "In the first step, the surface of a given sample was",
                "cleaned \"in situ\" by Kr sputtering at 35 keV removing",
                "typically about 300 monolayers."
              ]
            }
          ],
