                "Ue - screening potential energy (eV).",
                "N/Eff - a number of valence electrons per metallic atom",
                "material   Temp       Ue         solubility     N/Eff",
                "  Pt        20      675+/-70        0.06",
                "           100      530+/-40        0.06",
                "           200      530+/-40        0.05",
                "           300      465+/-38        0.04",
                "           340      480+/-70        0.04",
                "  Co        20      640+/-70        0.14",
                "           200      480+/-60        0.02",
                "  Ti       -10      <30             2.1",
                "            50      <50             1.1",
                "           100      250+/-40        0.26",
                "           150      295+/-40        0.23",
                "           200      290+/-65        0.20     1.7+/-0.7",
                "  Sc       200      320+/-50        0.11      2.6+/-0.8",
                "  Y        200      270+/-75        0.09      2.6+/-1.4",
                "  Zr       200      205+/-70        0.13      1.1+/-0.7",
                "  Lu       200      265+/-70        0.08      2.2+/-1.2",
                "  Hf       200      370+/-70        0.04      4.0+/-1.5",
                "  La       200      245+/-70        0.09      2.4+/-1.4",
                "  Ce       200      200+/-50        0.11      1.5+/-0.7",
                "  Nd       200      190+/-50        0.08      1.4+/-0.7",
                "  Sm       200      314+/-60        0.08      3.5+/-1.3",
                "  Eu       200      120+/-60        0.05      0.8+/-0.8",
                "  Gd       200      340+/-85        0.08      4.2+/-2.1",
                "  Tb       200      340+/-80        0.18      3.9+/-1.8",
                "  Dy       200      340+/-70        0.09      4.9+/-2.0",
                "  Ho       200      165+/-50        0.07      0.9+/-0.5",
                "  Er       200      360+/-80        0.05      4.3+/-1.9",
                "  Tm       200      260+/-80        0.05      2.2+/-1.4",
                "  Yb       200      110+/-40        0.13      0.4+/-0.3",
                "  C        200        <50           0.15",
                "-by authors.  The absolute beam energy uncertainty",
                "leads to a negligible uncertainty in the d(d,p)t cross",
